        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-09T20:22:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh, I actually considered the prevented attack scenario, but I had thought that the \"unrelated\" `code_verifier` check would nevertheless fail on OpenIDProvider side when we request refresh token: the verifier bytes we provide would produce different SHA2 than what OpenIDPRovider should have associated with the access code. And since the verifier bytes are essentially a high entropy nonce, this should equivalent to nonce.\n\nNow, while I\u0027d appreciate learning what I missed, I don\u0027t see any problem with what is implemented.",
      "parentUuid": "59df004a_767f59ef",
      "revId": "34784a384199eee5e8a33fe2e104a03ba0683427",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "16065e46_e471f029",
        "filename": "server/encryptedcookies/method.go",
