        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-04-09T16:33:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The callback here can be called many times due to trans retries.\nA prior try could actually have been successful, in which case *this* very session would have been written.\n\u003d\u003e errCodeReuse looks not quite correct to me in this case, though correct in most others cases.\n\n\u003d\u003e\nIF you think it\u0027s OK to ~ignore the case above,\n  then please document.\nELSE \n  IIUC checking that s.Generation \u003d\u003d 1 and encryptedPrivate match should suffice to assert that prior try wrote it. Right?",
